@odedharth I've spent ages trying to setup automated build for dlib on ios.
You can generate an Xcode project using CMake, but then you have to manually open it and change SDK to iOS. I tried different iOS CMake toolchains but none of them have worked.

The easiest and most reliable way to add dlib to ios app is to add `source.cpp` to Xcode source files and add dlib folder to header files search path.

