@idella I don't know about routes, but what happened here is that 2.4.1 is the first release that I prepared, and I suspect I did it differently than the other maintainers.

I was using `python setup.py sdist` generates the source distribution containing only the source actually used in the package, plus anything declared in the manifest (cuts out irrelevant metadata like say the travis configuration, etc). The problem is that the test suite is not a standard part of the module and it was not included in the manifest, so the script didn't include it. Evidently the other maintainers were creating the source distribution by some other method.

I'll manually add the test suite to the 2.4.1 source distributions and re-upload them, then add the tests to the manifest for the next release (likely 2.5.0).

