For future reference: Note that the following APIs let clients control how the memory allocated to global data-structures is managed:

           void Z3_API Z3_finalize_memory(void);

The above API function can be used for memory leak detection and also in contexts where the memory overhead of a library has to be controlled.

           void Z3_API Z3_reset_memory(void);

This above API first de-allocates all internal structures. It then re-allocates internal tables (this time they are empty). It can be used for situations where the use of persistent tables leads to memory pressure. 



